Title:
WSL, COM Hooking, & RTTI

Type:
Blog Post

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
- The post explains how to obtain reliable telemetry for WSL process creation by hooking the WSL COM server (wslservice.exe), specifically the `ILxssUserSession::CreateLxProcess` method.  
- It addresses the problem that wslservice.exe ships without symbols and that ETW/TraceLogging providers don’t reliably expose WSL2 activity, making traditional monitoring difficult.  
- The author uses MSVC Run-Time Type Information (RTTI) metadata embedded in the binary to locate the COM interface vtable at runtime (TypeDescriptor → Complete Object Locator → vtable), then patches the target vtable slot.  
- It highlights that hooking `CreateLxProcess` captures both WSL1 and WSL2 flows because the COM interface is shared, even though the backend differs (Pico provider vs Hyper-V).  
- A POC DLL (`WslHook.dll`) logs client PID/process/SID, command line args, distro/instance IDs, and handles, demonstrating visibility into WSL execution without relying on `wsl.exe` telemetry.  
- Useful for red teams and defenders/researchers needing WSL execution visibility, and for reverse engineers dealing with symbol-less COM servers.

Technical Focus:
- WSL COM architecture (client → wslservice.exe → backend dispatch)
- COM interface vtable hooking (`ILxssUserSession::CreateLxProcess`)
- MSVC RTTI structures (`_RTTITypeDescriptor`, `_RTTICompleteObjectLocator`)
- Binary scanning using RVAs to resolve vtables without symbols
- Vtable slot/offset validation across IDL versions and builds
- Telemetry/logging via `OutputDebugStringW` (with ETW suggested for production)

Use Cases:
- Detect/monitor WSL command execution that bypasses launching `wsl.exe`
- Build EDR-style user-mode sensors for WSL activity in wslservice.exe
- Reverse engineer and hook COM methods in symbol-less Windows binaries
- Validate/triage offensive tradecraft leveraging `CreateLxProcess` for stealthy WSL execution
- Research WSL1 vs WSL2 execution paths and parameter marshaling

Keywords:
WSL, WSL2, WSL1, wslservice.exe, wsl.exe, COM, ILxssUserSession, CreateLxProcess, vtable hooking, RTTI, MSVC, _RTTITypeDescriptor, _RTTICompleteObjectLocator, RVA, IDA Pro, reverse engineering, HvSocket, Hyper-V, TraceLogging, ETW, OutputDebugStringW, Detours